nib.text:
Four men were shot in Elmhurst Sunday afternoon, officials said.

At 1:36 p.m., police responded to a report of a shooting near 41st Avenue and Warren Street.

Upon arrival, officers found four men with gunshot wounds.

Medics took them all to a local hospital, where one man was listed in critical condition, [PIX11 reported](https://pix11.com/news/local-news/queens/4-people-shot-in-queens-cops-say/).

The suspects fled on a moped, police said.

No arrests have been made. This investigation is ongoing.
